      "content": "Focus on verifying that all base plates and mudsills are level and sitting on solid ground, ensuring mudsills extend fully under the footprint of the scaffolding. Check for plumb and square connection standards, as well as the integrity of beam locking at any connections between elements. For residential settings in particular, double-check that toeboards and guardrails are securely installed at the correct heights to prevent falls. Finally, ensure all access ladders or cleats are properly tied to prevent slip hazards before allowing any personnel to climb the structure.",
