      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the ground is uneven or soft after rain, you must place full-depth mudsills that extend beyond the framework to spread the load, and then install adjustable screw jacks on these mudsills to ensure a perfectly rigid level surface. Before placing any scaffolding, you should verify the ground can support the load and add hydraulic rollers if you cannot achieve full contact with solid ground, but first prepare the soil by breaking up large clumps or filling small depressions. Never skip a final visual inspection of the entire base after it rains, and consult your supplier or local OSHA guidelines if the soil shear strength is compromised.",
